1
00:00:00,058 --> 00:00:06,064
(Bell chime)

2
00:00:13,655 --> 00:00:15,657
(Sonoko Suzuki) Congratulations, Masaru-san!

3
00:00:15,741 --> 00:00:17,743
(Ran Mouri) Congratulations to you both.

4
00:00:18,368 --> 00:00:20,454
(Crowd cheering)

5
00:00:20,537 --> 00:00:22,456
(Conan Edogawa) Ha ha... Huh?

6
00:00:30,088 --> 00:00:36,094
♪~

7
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,522
(Conan)
The shadow's blackness and the darkness's depth,
The light of deduction cuts right through.

8
00:00:46,605 --> 00:00:50,317
A gunshot aimed at the bride and groom,
Solve the impossible crime's mystery.

9
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,902
See through to the one single truth.

10
00:00:51,985 --> 00:00:53,904
Looks like a child, mind of an adult.

11
00:00:53,987 --> 00:00:56,740
His name is Detective Conan!

12
00:02:22,123 --> 00:02:28,129
~♪

10
00:02:29,986 --> 00:02:35,186
"The Wedding Reception and Two Gunshots"

13
00:02:48,024 --> 00:02:51,027
Hmm, the food's pretty good.

14
00:02:51,111 --> 00:02:53,363
But, honestly, was it really okay for complete strangers—

15
00:02:53,446 --> 00:02:56,866
like us to come?

16
00:02:57,617 --> 00:02:59,410
It's fine, it's fine.

17
00:02:59,786 --> 00:03:01,412
If I'd come alone—

18
00:03:01,496 --> 00:03:03,665
which table do you think they'd have stuck me at?

19
00:03:04,165 --> 00:03:07,293
Nothing but stuffy old men and ladies, right?

20
00:03:07,377 --> 00:03:10,672
And besides, if I come to one of these things by myself—

21
00:03:10,755 --> 00:03:13,216
people trying to introduce their sons to me

22
00:03:13,299 --> 00:03:16,094
come up to greet me one after another—

23
00:03:16,427 --> 00:03:19,264
I can never eat in peace.

24
00:03:20,181 --> 00:03:24,310
Wow, even a financial conglomerate heiress has it tough.

25
00:03:25,270 --> 00:03:29,190
Yeah. I'm sure Masaru-san must have had the same experience.

26
00:03:29,274 --> 00:03:31,568
And then he fell in love at first sight—

27
00:03:31,651 --> 00:03:33,778
with the woman managing the villa...

28
00:03:34,237 --> 00:03:36,322
So romantic!

29
00:03:36,614 --> 00:03:38,283
Ha ha ha ha...

30
00:03:40,869 --> 00:03:44,205
Ladies and gentlemen, I apologize for interrupting your conversations.

31
00:03:44,622 --> 00:03:49,210
We would now like to receive congratulatory addresses from our distinguished guests—

32
00:03:49,294 --> 00:03:51,713
but before that, we have an announcement for everyone.

33
00:03:51,796 --> 00:03:52,839
Huh?

34
00:03:54,007 --> 00:03:58,178
The groom, Masaru-san, and the bride, Miho-san—

35
00:03:58,261 --> 00:04:01,681
who just held their solemn wedding ceremony at the chapel earlier—

36
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:07,353
actually submitted their marriage registration at the ward office the day before yesterday.

37
00:04:07,437 --> 00:04:09,314
Oooh!
What?

38
00:04:09,397 --> 00:04:11,024
Mother, did you hear about this?

39
00:04:11,357 --> 00:04:14,527
No, I didn't know either.

40
00:04:14,611 --> 00:04:16,529
Honestly, doing whatever they please...

41
00:04:16,946 --> 00:04:19,240
Everyone, once more for the couple—

42
00:04:19,324 --> 00:04:21,743
please give them a huge round of applause!

43
00:04:26,831 --> 00:04:28,374
What? Seriously...

44
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:29,626
We're out of wine.

45
00:04:29,709 --> 00:04:31,836
Hey, Arisa, you're drinking too much.

46
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,755
Oh, shut up, Dad.

47
00:04:33,838 --> 00:04:35,006
You insisted I come,

48
00:04:35,089 --> 00:04:36,341
so I came.

49
00:04:37,091 --> 00:04:40,678
She was one of the girls hoping to be Masaru-san's bride, too.

50
00:04:40,762 --> 00:04:41,930
Really...

51
00:04:42,013 --> 00:04:45,558
That wine, right? I'll bring it right away.

52
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,686
Yoshifumi-kun.

53
00:04:48,770 --> 00:04:50,939
You're the bride's brother,

54
00:04:51,022 --> 00:04:52,941
you should let someone else handle it.

55
00:04:53,024 --> 00:04:55,109
No, I'm just... not really comfortable at these sorts of gatherings.

56
00:04:55,193 --> 00:04:56,444
I feel more at ease

57
00:04:56,527 --> 00:04:57,779
if I'm moving around.

58
00:04:57,862 --> 00:04:59,447
It's less stressful for me.

59
00:05:02,075 --> 00:05:03,243
Just for today, you could at least

60
00:05:03,326 --> 00:05:05,203
sit down and relax.

61
00:05:05,286 --> 00:05:07,914
In the end, a caretaker is still just a caretaker.

62
00:05:08,706 --> 00:05:12,168
Honestly, the thought of that woman

63
00:05:12,252 --> 00:05:14,379
doing whatever she wants with the Hatakeyama family fortune...

64
00:05:14,671 --> 00:05:17,465
Dad must be turning in his grave.

65
00:05:19,092 --> 00:05:22,929
Now, we will receive a congratulatory address from the groom Masaru-san's uncle—

66
00:05:23,012 --> 00:05:24,472
President of Hatakeyama Bank,

67
00:05:24,931 --> 00:05:28,393
Kenshiro Hatakeyama-sama.

68
00:05:28,476 --> 00:05:30,853
(Applause)

69
00:05:31,771 --> 00:05:33,439
What's wrong, Conan-kun?

70
00:05:33,523 --> 00:05:35,108
Just... restroom.

71
00:05:40,029 --> 00:05:41,614
Hey there, little guy.
Huh?

72
00:05:42,115 --> 00:05:44,284
What's up? Looking for the bathroom?

73
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:46,619
Yeah.
Do you know where it is?

74
00:05:46,703 --> 00:05:47,787
I'm fine.

75
00:05:48,746 --> 00:05:53,334
You're... the kid who came with the young lady from the Suzuki financial group, right?

76
00:05:53,418 --> 00:05:57,880
Yeah. Hey, you're the caretaker of this villa, aren't you, big brother?

77
00:05:57,964 --> 00:06:01,718
Ah. Well, originally, when this villa was first built—

78
00:06:01,801 --> 00:06:05,513
my old man and my mom became the caretakers, but—

79
00:06:05,596 --> 00:06:08,308
both of them died in an accident.

80
00:06:08,391 --> 00:06:11,269
Huh... What did you do before that?

81
00:06:11,769 --> 00:06:13,146
We were farmers.

82
00:06:13,229 --> 00:06:17,233
But around here, the damage from monkeys and wild boars was awful.

83
00:06:17,442 --> 00:06:21,154
Partly because of that, we quit farming and became caretakers.

84
00:06:21,237 --> 00:06:22,530
Hmm.

85
00:06:22,613 --> 00:06:24,782
Anyway, little guy, shouldn't you be getting to the restroom?

86
00:06:24,866 --> 00:06:27,869
Ah! I forgot. See ya.

87
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:37,754
...is what I told them!
Hey, how's it going?

88
00:06:38,504 --> 00:06:41,507
Was the food to your liking?

89
00:06:41,591 --> 00:06:44,844
Yes, we're completely stuffed, thank you!

90
00:06:44,927 --> 00:06:46,304
Oh, glad to hear it.

91
00:06:46,804 --> 00:06:49,640
When we get back from our honeymoon—

92
00:06:49,724 --> 00:06:52,810
you three should come visit our house in Tokyo.

93
00:06:52,894 --> 00:06:56,439
We'd love to, but we're counting on you for souvenirs!

94
00:06:56,522 --> 00:06:59,942
Ahaha! Got it, I'll remember.

95
00:07:00,026 --> 00:07:02,820
More importantly, is it okay to leave your bride alone?

96
00:07:02,904 --> 00:07:04,697
Staying beside two beauties like us—

97
00:07:04,781 --> 00:07:07,116
She might get jealous, you know?
Huh?

98
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:09,118
That's not true.

99
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:11,788
Because I trust Masaru-san.

100
00:07:11,871 --> 00:07:13,956
Ah~ Burning with passion!

101
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:17,168
Huh? Miho-san, you look a bit pale...

102
00:07:17,752 --> 00:07:20,671
Yes, I'm feeling a little tired.

103
00:07:20,755 --> 00:07:23,174
Then leave the rest to me—

104
00:07:23,257 --> 00:07:25,593
You should go back to the hotel and rest.

105
00:07:25,676 --> 00:07:27,428
Yoshifumi-kun.
Yes?

106
00:07:27,512 --> 00:07:29,055
Have you been drinking?

107
00:07:29,138 --> 00:07:31,391
No, I don't drink.

108
00:07:31,474 --> 00:07:32,809
Then, sorry to ask, but—

109
00:07:32,892 --> 00:07:35,728
could you take Miho in my car and drive her back?

110
00:07:35,812 --> 00:07:37,063
Understood.

111
00:07:43,361 --> 00:07:45,988
(Yawn)

112
00:07:46,531 --> 00:07:49,242
Maybe we should be heading out soon, too.

113
00:07:49,325 --> 00:07:52,954
Yeah. Let's say goodbye to Masaru-san...

114
00:07:53,037 --> 00:07:54,914
Huh? Where's Masaru-san?

115
00:07:54,997 --> 00:07:56,416
About ten minutes ago—

116
00:07:56,499 --> 00:07:59,419
he said, "It's a call from Miho-san," and went out.

117
00:07:59,502 --> 00:08:01,379
Th-this is terrible!

118
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:03,172
What's wrong?

119
00:08:03,631 --> 00:08:07,009
By the... by the van in the parking lot—

120
00:08:07,093 --> 00:08:09,303
th-the groom is collapsed there!

121
00:08:09,387 --> 00:08:12,056
What?!
What?! No way!

122
00:08:12,807 --> 00:08:14,475
What?
It can't be...

123
00:08:21,274 --> 00:08:22,275
Ah...!

124
00:08:25,194 --> 00:08:28,030
Shot at point-blank range with a gun.

125
00:08:28,114 --> 00:08:29,699
Masaru-san!

126
00:08:29,782 --> 00:08:33,244
Wait, don't get any closer until the police arrive.

127
00:08:33,327 --> 00:08:34,412
Conan-kun!

128
00:08:34,495 --> 00:08:37,373
Ran-neechan, hurry, call the police!

129
00:08:37,457 --> 00:08:38,624
Right.

130
00:08:38,958 --> 00:08:41,794
Is it true that Masaru-kun is down?!

131
00:08:42,336 --> 00:08:43,379
Old man...

132
00:08:43,463 --> 00:08:46,090
(Gunshot sound)
Ah!

133
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,050
What was that sound just now?

134
00:08:48,134 --> 00:08:49,927
It sounded like it came from across the river...

135
00:08:50,011 --> 00:08:52,472
Yeah, it was from the direction of the hotel.

136
00:08:52,555 --> 00:08:53,931
It can't be...

137
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,202
(Knock)

138
00:09:14,285 --> 00:09:16,621
Miho-san! Miho-san!

139
00:09:21,902 --> 00:09:23,028
Ah...!

140
00:09:26,698 --> 00:09:27,741
Ah...!

141
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:38,710
I see.

142
00:09:38,919 --> 00:09:41,671
So when that sound like a gunshot was heard—

143
00:09:41,755 --> 00:09:45,926
everyone here, besides Conan-kun, was gathered right here, correct?

144
00:09:46,009 --> 00:09:48,678
Yes, we received a call from Conan-kun—

145
00:09:48,762 --> 00:09:52,224
and he said, "Everyone should wait here for the police."

146
00:09:52,641 --> 00:09:55,644
Alright. Let's go check the other crime scene, then.

147
00:09:55,727 --> 00:09:56,728
Yes, sir.

148
00:10:05,695 --> 00:10:07,114
Hmm...

149
00:10:07,823 --> 00:10:10,117
(Sobbing)

150
00:10:17,499 --> 00:10:19,835
What are you doing, Takagi-keiji?

151
00:10:19,918 --> 00:10:24,131
Oh? Ah, just searching to see if the culprit left anything behind.

152
00:10:24,214 --> 00:10:26,508
I see~
Found something!

153
00:10:27,592 --> 00:10:30,220
This looks like it's definitely the murder weapon.

154
00:10:31,012 --> 00:10:33,473
Excuse me, can we get a photo of this?

155
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:36,893
Hm... Bamboo?

156
00:10:37,686 --> 00:10:39,771
Why would that be here...

157
00:10:41,648 --> 00:10:43,108
Tatsuya-kun.

158
00:10:43,191 --> 00:10:46,444
I hate to bring this up at a time like this, but—

159
00:10:47,028 --> 00:10:50,657
what's going to happen to the shares Masaru-kun holds?

160
00:10:50,740 --> 00:10:53,994
The biggest concern is the employees becoming uneasy.

161
00:10:54,536 --> 00:10:57,581
Well, since that boy didn't have any children—

162
00:10:57,664 --> 00:11:01,793
wouldn't they naturally go to me, his sister, or his mother?

163
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:03,253
No.

164
00:11:03,753 --> 00:11:07,465
Assuming Masaru-kun died before Miho-san—

165
00:11:07,549 --> 00:11:09,509
at the moment of Masaru-kun's death—

166
00:11:09,593 --> 00:11:12,304
all of his assets would belong to Miho-san.

167
00:11:12,721 --> 00:11:15,140
What? What do you mean?

168
00:11:15,223 --> 00:11:17,684
Didn't the wedding host announce it last night?

169
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:20,061
"The two have already registered their marriage."

170
00:11:20,145 --> 00:11:23,815
Wait, so what happens to Masaru's fortune?!

171
00:11:24,649 --> 00:11:27,861
If Miho-san died after Masaru-kun—

172
00:11:27,944 --> 00:11:31,448
then Miho-san's heirs would inherit it.

173
00:11:32,157 --> 00:11:36,203
What? That's ridiculous...

174
00:11:36,286 --> 00:11:39,456
I will absolutely never accept that!

175
00:11:39,956 --> 00:11:43,043
Accept it or not, that's the law.

176
00:11:43,585 --> 00:11:46,630
A stupid law like that is just wrong!

177
00:11:50,884 --> 00:11:54,054
Sorry to gather you all at a time like this.

178
00:11:55,055 --> 00:11:59,100
Our mother is resting in her room due to severe shock.

179
00:11:59,476 --> 00:12:01,061
Very well.

180
00:12:01,144 --> 00:12:03,396
Among the attendees from last night—

181
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:07,609
anyone with a solid alibi for the estimated time of death for both victims—

182
00:12:07,692 --> 00:12:09,611
has been allowed to go home for now.

183
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:12,614
Are you suspecting us?

184
00:12:12,948 --> 00:12:16,076
Yes. You are all particularly closely related

185
00:12:16,159 --> 00:12:19,037
to the two who have passed away, so—

186
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:23,500
while your anger is justified, please cooperate with the investigation.

187
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:27,504
Tatsuya-kun and I were beside Masaru-kun's body

188
00:12:27,587 --> 00:12:30,298
when Miho-san was killed.

189
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:33,885
At least regarding Miho-san's case, we have an alibi.

190
00:12:34,219 --> 00:12:38,682
Indeed. The bullets removed from the two victims' bodies—

191
00:12:38,765 --> 00:12:43,603
both match the handgun found in the flower bed.

192
00:12:43,687 --> 00:12:48,316
In other words, these two murders are believed to be the work of a single culprit.

193
00:12:48,858 --> 00:12:50,235
Then, we...

194
00:12:50,318 --> 00:12:53,738
However, at that time, Rikako-san and Arisa-san—

195
00:12:53,822 --> 00:12:56,116
had already returned to the hotel, hadn't you?

196
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:58,535
Are you saying I'm a murderer?!

197
00:12:58,827 --> 00:13:01,329
Now, now, please don't get agitated.

198
00:13:01,413 --> 00:13:03,456
It's merely a discussion of possibilities.

199
00:13:04,124 --> 00:13:08,920
Since it's still early in the investigation, we don't yet know the motive for killing

200
00:13:09,004 --> 00:13:11,506
the bride and groom one after the other.

201
00:13:12,048 --> 00:13:14,759
So, what we'd like to ask—

202
00:13:14,843 --> 00:13:16,928
Yoshifumi-san, the bride's younger brother.

203
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:19,723
Yes.

204
00:13:20,265 --> 00:13:23,935
According to the results of our investigation from last night until now—

205
00:13:24,269 --> 00:13:26,521
you have outstanding debts of several million yen

206
00:13:26,604 --> 00:13:30,066
across multiple financial institutions, is that correct?

207
00:13:30,358 --> 00:13:32,610
Ah... That's...

208
00:13:33,403 --> 00:13:36,448
Whether that's true or not, could you please answer?

209
00:13:37,991 --> 00:13:40,410
Yes... Yes, I do.

210
00:13:40,493 --> 00:13:43,580
But I didn't kill anyone!

211
00:13:43,663 --> 00:13:45,749
Why would I kill my own sister...?

212
00:13:46,249 --> 00:13:48,460
When she's my only family left...

213
00:13:52,255 --> 00:13:54,716
Ah, Chiba-keiji, what were you doing?

214
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:58,678
Conan-kun, I was checking the security footage.

215
00:13:58,762 --> 00:14:02,432
See, that security camera installed on the inside of the entrance—

216
00:14:02,515 --> 00:14:05,477
it should have captured the area near the flower bed where the gun was found, right?

217
00:14:06,019 --> 00:14:09,981
So I thought, and I watched all the recordings from last night, but—

218
00:14:10,065 --> 00:14:12,484
No one approached the flower bed.

219
00:14:12,776 --> 00:14:15,779
Huh? Then how did the gun end up there?

220
00:14:16,446 --> 00:14:20,033
Maybe they threw it from a window on the upper floor of the hotel.

221
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:26,373
Hm?

222
00:14:27,957 --> 00:14:30,627
What are these four dents?

223
00:14:33,338 --> 00:14:34,381
Ah!

224
00:14:36,341 --> 00:14:38,009
Oh yeah, last night—

225
00:14:38,093 --> 00:14:42,680
we got a call that the streetlight over there was out, so I came by.

226
00:14:42,764 --> 00:14:44,891
Did you see anything at that time?

227
00:14:44,974 --> 00:14:47,394
Umm, now that you mention it...

228
00:14:52,190 --> 00:14:54,025
(Door closing sound)
Hm?

229
00:14:56,611 --> 00:14:58,279
About what time was that?

230
00:14:58,363 --> 00:15:01,908
Hm? Erm, let's see...

231
00:15:02,158 --> 00:15:06,037
Ah! I got the call at 9:40, so—

232
00:15:06,121 --> 00:15:08,331
it must have been around 9:45.

233
00:15:08,832 --> 00:15:13,420
9:45...
What's the significance of that time?

235
00:15:14,462 --> 00:15:16,589
9:45, you say?

236
00:15:16,673 --> 00:15:19,634
That's just after Miho-san left the villa—

237
00:15:19,717 --> 00:15:23,638
a full 30 minutes before we found Masaru-san's body.

238
00:15:23,721 --> 00:15:24,764
Hm...

239
00:15:30,311 --> 00:15:32,188
So that's it.

240
00:15:32,605 --> 00:15:34,732
Ah! But, if that's the case, then that thing...

241
00:15:34,816 --> 00:15:36,943
Hey~ little boy!
Huh?

242
00:15:37,402 --> 00:15:40,488
A kid shouldn't be wandering around at this hour.

243
00:15:40,572 --> 00:15:42,073
Sorry.

244
00:15:42,449 --> 00:15:45,410
There are hungry monkeys roaming around this area—

245
00:15:45,493 --> 00:15:46,995
you'll get bitten.

246
00:15:47,078 --> 00:15:48,121
Ha!

247
00:15:48,538 --> 00:15:51,291
I see... If we use that...

248
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:54,794
There's no way we could have killed Masaru!

249
00:15:54,878 --> 00:15:57,672
Deep down, you wanted to push Masaru-san out and put your own husband

250
00:15:57,755 --> 00:16:00,884
at the top of the Hatakeyama Group, right?

251
00:16:00,967 --> 00:16:02,635
We know all about it.

252
00:16:02,927 --> 00:16:05,889
Don't say stupid things, you foolish girl!

253
00:16:06,264 --> 00:16:07,599
You're the one who couldn't become Masaru's wife,

254
00:16:07,682 --> 00:16:09,767
so you killed Miho-san...

255
00:16:09,851 --> 00:16:12,937
and then killed Masaru when he found out, didn't you?!

256
00:16:13,188 --> 00:16:14,772
Who's the fool here?

257
00:16:14,856 --> 00:16:17,609
Masaru-san was killed first!

258
00:16:17,692 --> 00:16:20,487
Has your greed for money driven you completely crazy?

259
00:16:21,821 --> 00:16:22,822
Ah!

260
00:16:22,906 --> 00:16:26,159
Stop this shameful display right now!

261
00:16:26,242 --> 00:16:28,745
Inspector Megure!
Ye... Yes?

262
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,705
Can we go home now...?

263
00:16:30,788 --> 00:16:32,832
(Tranquilizer dart sound)
Oww... Funya...

264
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:35,752
Sonoko, here it comes? That usual thing...

265
00:16:36,044 --> 00:16:37,670
Funyanyo...

266
00:16:38,129 --> 00:16:41,382
I don't want to say unnecessary things either, but—

267
00:16:41,466 --> 00:16:44,802
if I stay silent now, the real culprit benefits the most, right?

268
00:16:45,136 --> 00:16:49,474
S-Sonoko-kun... Are you saying you've figured out who the real culprit is?

269
00:16:49,766 --> 00:16:50,975
What?!

270
00:16:51,059 --> 00:16:55,230
Yes. If the police would just hurry up and arrest that person—

271
00:16:55,313 --> 00:16:58,525
I wouldn't have to act like a know-it-all.

272
00:16:58,608 --> 00:17:00,026
Rikako-san.

273
00:17:00,109 --> 00:17:03,112
You said one thing that was correct.

274
00:17:03,196 --> 00:17:04,239
Huh?

275
00:17:04,322 --> 00:17:07,492
Miho-san was killed first.

276
00:17:07,575 --> 00:17:08,868
What?

277
00:17:08,952 --> 00:17:13,414
But the only ones who returned to the hotel first were Rikako-san and Arisa-san...

278
00:17:13,498 --> 00:17:15,375
I told you, it wasn't me!

279
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:16,626
Me neither!

280
00:17:17,377 --> 00:17:19,629
I know it wasn't either of you.

281
00:17:19,879 --> 00:17:20,880
Hmph!

282
00:17:20,964 --> 00:17:25,134
The time of the murder was shortly after Miho-san arrived at the cottage.

283
00:17:25,218 --> 00:17:28,388
That's why she hadn't changed out of her dress.

284
00:17:28,638 --> 00:17:31,266
You likely drove Miho-san there—

285
00:17:31,349 --> 00:17:33,685
and killed her immediately, didn't you?

286
00:17:33,768 --> 00:17:34,852
Yoshifumi-san?

287
00:17:34,936 --> 00:17:36,062
Ha...

288
00:17:36,729 --> 00:17:38,523
What are you talking about?

289
00:17:38,815 --> 00:17:41,901
You're drowning in massive debt.

290
00:17:42,193 --> 00:17:44,320
When your older sister's marriage was decided—

291
00:17:44,404 --> 00:17:47,282
you thought this would let you repay those debts, but—

292
00:17:47,365 --> 00:17:50,326
things didn't go so smoothly.

293
00:17:51,077 --> 00:17:55,081
So, you slipped something into your sister's drink.

294
00:17:55,164 --> 00:17:58,585
When she started feeling unwell, you drove her to the cottage—

295
00:17:59,085 --> 00:18:01,838
and killed her with a hidden handgun.

296
00:18:02,297 --> 00:18:04,632
Muffling the sound with a cushion or something.

297
00:18:04,716 --> 00:18:05,800
(Gunshot sound)

298
00:18:05,883 --> 00:18:10,096
After that, you used Miho-san's cell phone to call Masaru-san out—

299
00:18:10,179 --> 00:18:12,974
and killed him the same way.

300
00:18:13,516 --> 00:18:14,642
(Gunshot sound)

301
00:18:15,184 --> 00:18:19,439
Wait a minute. What about the murder weapon, the handgun?

302
00:18:19,522 --> 00:18:21,899
It was found in the hotel flower bed, right?

303
00:18:21,983 --> 00:18:23,443
Until the police came—

304
00:18:23,526 --> 00:18:26,446
wasn't I with everyone else beside Masaru-san?

305
00:18:26,529 --> 00:18:29,449
I had no chance to get rid of the gun!

306
00:18:29,782 --> 00:18:32,493
That's the part that bothered me most, too.

307
00:18:32,577 --> 00:18:35,955
Why did the culprit discard the gun in a place like that?

308
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,833
And then I understood.

309
00:18:38,916 --> 00:18:41,544
The gun wasn't thrown to that location—

310
00:18:41,628 --> 00:18:43,254
it fell there.

311
00:18:43,338 --> 00:18:44,505
Ah...!

312
00:18:45,465 --> 00:18:49,719
The villa and the hotel are almost directly opposite each other across the river, right?

313
00:18:49,802 --> 00:18:52,263
But after killing Masaru-san—

314
00:18:52,347 --> 00:18:55,850
throwing the handgun to the opposite bank is physically impossible by human strength.

315
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:58,269
So, you used that thing.

316
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,610
(Sound of falling)

317
00:19:06,069 --> 00:19:08,029
How could I have done something like that...?

318
00:19:08,279 --> 00:19:09,781
Isn't it obvious?

319
00:19:09,864 --> 00:19:12,450
Rikako-san and the others were just saying it earlier.

320
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:14,786
To make it look as though Masaru-san's fortune

321
00:19:14,869 --> 00:19:17,580
was first inherited by Miho-san—

322
00:19:17,664 --> 00:19:19,165
it was absolutely necessary that Miho-san

323
00:19:19,248 --> 00:19:23,127
appeared to have died after Masaru-san.

324
00:19:23,211 --> 00:19:24,253
For that to work,

325
00:19:24,337 --> 00:19:28,132
the handgun needed to be found on this side of the river.

326
00:19:28,549 --> 00:19:32,720
Th-that's just speculation! Do you have any proof?

327
00:19:33,304 --> 00:19:36,224
Do you remember the old man with the stepladder?

328
00:19:36,307 --> 00:19:37,350
Huh?

329
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,894
The hotel employee who came to change the fluorescent light

330
00:19:39,977 --> 00:19:42,313
on the path near the cottage—

331
00:19:42,397 --> 00:19:45,983
he remembered seeing a figure rush out of that room.

332
00:19:46,651 --> 00:19:50,238
Before Masaru-san was even killed.

333
00:19:50,321 --> 00:19:53,783
Meaning, Miho-san was the one murdered first.

334
00:19:53,866 --> 00:19:58,287
Then what was that gunshot everyone heard in the parking lot?!

335
00:19:58,371 --> 00:20:00,456
That gunshot is precisely—

336
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:04,794
the very centerpiece of the alibi you worked so hard to create.

337
00:20:05,628 --> 00:20:08,089
Go ahead, you can come in.

338
00:20:08,172 --> 00:20:10,299
Ah... uh...

339
00:20:10,758 --> 00:20:12,969
Looks like you recognize it.

340
00:20:13,052 --> 00:20:16,931
It's only natural, since it was found in your family's shed.

341
00:20:17,014 --> 00:20:19,434
Wha... what is that?

342
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:21,436
It's a bird-scarer.

343
00:20:21,519 --> 00:20:24,397
It's a tool that uses fireworks to scare away

344
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:27,775
sparrows that come to eat the rice grain in autumn.

345
00:20:28,234 --> 00:20:32,238
Around here, they seem to use it to scare off monkeys.

346
00:20:34,157 --> 00:20:35,742
While we're at it, I should mention—

347
00:20:35,825 --> 00:20:39,162
it was set to make a sound only once.

348
00:20:39,245 --> 00:20:41,956
That's what everyone heard.

349
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:48,421
Damn it... It's my sister's fault!

350
00:20:48,504 --> 00:20:52,383
Becoming part of a family worth billions—

351
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:55,511
and yet she wouldn't do anything for me...

352
00:20:55,595 --> 00:20:58,306
How could she be so cruel?

353
00:20:58,389 --> 00:21:04,020
(Sobbing)

354
00:21:04,395 --> 00:21:10,401
♪~

355
00:22:18,177 --> 00:22:23,933
~♪

356
00:22:30,231 --> 00:22:33,776
Ran's completely devastated.

357
00:22:33,860 --> 00:22:38,281
Well, after what happened, I guess that's only natural.

358
00:22:38,364 --> 00:22:39,407
Ran-neechan!

359
00:22:39,490 --> 00:22:42,535
Let's eat something delicious tonight and cheer up!

360
00:22:42,618 --> 00:22:45,162
If you want, I can even make it.

361
00:22:45,246 --> 00:22:47,832
I saw this cooking show on TV the other day—

362
00:22:47,915 --> 00:22:51,294
they showed how to make curry with a special twist.

363
00:22:52,336 --> 00:22:56,674
No, no, curry is off-limits! It's surprisingly high in calories.

364
00:22:56,757 --> 00:23:00,636
Sigh... Even though such a sad event just happened—

365
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:02,930
when I got back from the wedding and weighed myself—

366
00:23:03,723 --> 00:23:07,727
I'd gained two kilos. Shocking, right? Two whole kilos!

367
00:23:08,144 --> 00:23:11,647
Ha ha ha...
So *that's* why she was down.

368
00:23:11,731 --> 00:23:13,024
Ran!

369
00:23:13,608 --> 00:23:15,192
Good morning.

370
00:23:15,276 --> 00:23:17,737
Morning... Sigh...

371
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:20,364
Sonoko, you look tired.

372
00:23:20,448 --> 00:23:23,451
Listen to this. When I got back from the wedding and weighed myself—

373
00:23:23,534 --> 00:23:26,454
I'd gained three kilos!

374
00:23:26,537 --> 00:23:30,374
I gained two. We have to lose it before summer...

375
00:23:30,458 --> 00:23:32,376
We won't fit into our swimsuits!

376
00:23:32,710 --> 00:23:36,631
But hey, don't we have like, a weigh-in or something before that?

377
00:23:36,923 --> 00:23:39,842
Aaah...
Ran, what do we do?!

378
00:23:39,926 --> 00:23:42,803
Ugh... Exercise! We'll run, Sonoko!

379
00:23:43,387 --> 00:23:45,014
Let's go!

380
00:23:46,349 --> 00:23:50,811
Good grief. I'm worrying so much, I'm the one who's gonna lose weight.

381
00:23:52,104 --> 00:23:54,357
Oh wow! The cherry blossoms are in full bloom!

382
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:56,776
It's the perfect day for flower viewing!

383
00:23:58,361 --> 00:23:59,737
G-Great fortune?!

384
00:24:00,029 --> 00:24:01,238
Heh heh.

385
00:24:01,572 --> 00:24:04,951
Th-this is terrible, Shinichi! It's murder!

386
00:24:05,034 --> 00:24:08,287
It seems I have witnessed a murder!

375
00:24:11,336 --> 00:24:14,336
A 5 yen coin painted black with a Sharpie...

376
00:24:14,336 --> 00:24:16,336
Kurobei!

377
00:24:16,336 --> 00:24:18,236
Next Conan Special,

378
00:24:18,236 --> 00:24:21,636
"Tribute to Jodie and the Flower Viewing Trap".

379
00:24:37,136 --> 00:24:39,736
Next Conan's Hint:

380
00:24:39,736 --> 00:24:41,436
"5 yen coins".

391
00:24:41,681 --> 00:24:43,391
Next week is a one-hour special.

392
00:24:43,474 --> 00:24:48,644
The FBI, the Men in Black... it's packed.
